Question: Finding a family doctor or getting a health card (OHIP card)
Answer: VWAT can help you get a family doctor or health card. You can call us at 647-343-8928, ext. 116, fill out our contact form, or book an appointment here. A settlement worker will get back to assist you. We aim to respond within 1 to 2 business days.

Question: Personal income tax filing
Answer: VWAT has partnered with the Community Volunteer Income Tax Program (CVITP) since 2017 to offer a free income tax clinic in Toronto. Our experienced tax advisors provide guidance to make the process stress-free, helping you organize your documents and answer any questions. To access our free tax clinic, you can call us at 647-343-8928, ext. 116, or book an appointment online here. Note: For assistance with filing 2022 or earlier tax years, please select Thuy Nguyen. For 2023 or later tax years, you may choose any tax preparer.

Question: Why should I donate to VWAT?
Answer: Your donation helps to improve the lives of people who have moved to Canada. We've been helping our community since 1982 and appreciate all the support we have received over the last 40 years! We issue tax receipts for donations that are $20 and over.
